SIMPLE: evenness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Evenness
<hw>E"ven*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of being ven, level,
or disturbed; smoothness; horizontal position; uniformity; impartiality;
calmness; equanimity; appropriate place or level; <as>as,
<ex>evenness</ex> of surface, of a fluid at rest, of motion, of
dealings, of temper, of condition</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It had need be something extraordinary, that must warrant an
ordinary person to rise higher than his own <qex>evenness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Evensong</ent>⟦br⟧
